<br>
1. Correcting spelling and grammer gets us nowhere.<br>
<br>
2. These allegations have absolutely no evidence, credibility, or motive. Show me a screenshot, some eyewitnesses with screenshots, some logs (yes, I am well aware they can be edited) or anything else concrete. <br>
<br>
3. You are upset about some &quot;name calling&quot; and you bring it here hoping for an &quot;apology&quot;?  I am sorry, but this certainly isn't 3rd grade, and I don't care if your dad can beat up my dad. My guild will not apologize to you. I won't ask anyone to, I won't suggest it, hell I won't even agree with it if they do. <br>
<br>
At first I thought the concern here was that your camp had been stolen. That is absolutely something I will not condone. I will speak and be certain that this did not occur, and if it did, there will be an apology for that. <br>
<br>
4. If you do want to improve Blood Cults reputation, try the following. (Note, in my experience Blood Cult has been fine, but then again, I don't follow wild accusations.)<br>
  <br>
  a. Stop airing their dirty laundry in the public forums.<br>
  b. Don't act like a 4 year old and ask for an apology for some name calling.<br>
  c. Deal with problems like an adult, and people will likely be more responsive to you. Too many people cry about little problems they should simply deal with on their own without dragging the rest of us into your little drama.  <br>
<br>
I am an officer of HC, but the bulk of these opinions belong to me alone. I assure you the other officers will agree with the beginning of this post, and that is all that matters from a guild PR standpoint.<br>
