<br>
Your post seemed harmless to me until you flat out lied. You and your group NEVER did a camp check in /ooc or any other channel, you merely zoned in proceeded to go wherever you pleased. Before your group zoned in there were 9 people in the zone, three from my group and 6 from another guild's group.<br>
<br>
Gilama's group had been in planks all night and had only come to the zone in to pick up some new members. I don't think it's unreasonable for her to have to do that. We returned to her camp to find your group there claiming it was your camp. You left the camp after pulling only one mob and for that I thank you. Why you left without much of a fight only tells me you guys knew you were in the wrong and wished to correct your mistake.<br>
<br>
As for Mousee, I don't know anything about his history but I will say he acted honorably last night in looting the Boots of Flowing Slime and returning to the group after our CR so they could be randomed to one of the casters.<br>
<br>
The other matters last night that were discussed in /ooc I really have no knowledge of. Grithinnn apparently has issues with BC that occured prior to his joining HC, he's entitled to his opinion and I really doubt any harm can come from anything he said as there were only a hand full of people in the zone at the time.<br>
<br>
As for bringing the Honored Circle into this as the party for blame your again mistaken, we had a pickup group last night it wasn't a guild group. Your issues are with the individuals in question not with my guild. There were four guilds represented in our group not just one.<br>
<br>
Expecting an apology from my Guild or I is rather amusing. We did nothing wrong. I will not apologize for anything that was said about your guild either. I will not censor someone for relaying past experiences with members of your guild. <p>Opaque Anthemist<BR>
